cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with congestion control protocols and active queue management in a network setting.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a system level solution to reinstate priorities among protocols, which could involve information theory concepts.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper studies a fluid model that describes system dynamics of congestion control protocols competing on a bottleneck link governed by AQM.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper explores the negative interplay between scheduling/AQM techniques and low-priority congestion control protocols, which can impact system performance.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve multimedia traffic in the network setting.
